The method should return an integer value representing the number of valid words in the sentence.
The method should ignore leading and trailing spaces in the sentence.
The method should consider a word as valid if it consists of alphabetic characters only.
The method should consider a word as valid even if it contains punctuation marks within it.
The method should consider a word as separate if it is separated by spaces or punctuation marks.
The method should not count repeated words multiple times.
The method should handle uppercase and lowercase letters as equivalent when determining the validity of a word.
